> Virtualization (improvement):

    Idea: split one big machine into multiple virtual machines (VMs)

    how it works:
    -------------
    Hardware -> Hypervisor -> VM1, VM2, VM3
    Each VM -> OS -> APP
        - each VM has its own OS,
        - its own resources
        - full isolation

        Good things:
        ------------
        - full isolation
        - better resource usage
        - multiple apps on one machine

        Problems:
        ---------
        - heavyweight (each vm has full OS -> consumes RAM + CPU)
        - slow (vm takes time to start (boot OS))
        - works in DEV <-> Not working in QA

        Why:
        ----
        - different OS versions
        - missing configs
        - dependency issues

        Famous line:
        -------------
        - it works on my machine
        - it works in my environment
